==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rowen
<hw>Row"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. E.
<ets>rough</ets>, OE. <ets>row</ets>, <ets>rowe</ets>.]</ety> [Called
also <altname>rowet</altname>, <altname>rowett</altname>,
<altname>rowings</altname>, <altname>roughings</altname>.] <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A stubble field left unplowed till late in the autumn, that it may
be cropped by cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Turn your cows, that give milk, into your <qex>rowens</qex> till
snow comes.</q> <rj><qau>Mortimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The second growth of grass in a season;
aftermath.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rower</ent>⟦br⟧
